HELP ANDCASE                                        Fran Evelyn, July 1985

    switchon <start-condition>
        <one or more CASE or NOTCASE clauses>
        <optional ELSE clause>
    endswitchon

The word ANDCASE is used as part of the macro *SWITCHON. SWITCHON permits
abbreviation of multi-branch conditional statements where part of the
condition is the same for all branches.

See also HELP
    *CASE - also part of *SWITCHON
